How to add mods? **Make sure they are .jar files**

1. Go to your preferred Minecraft Mod distributor: Modrenth/Forge/etc

2. Look for mods that are compatible with your server: Fabric/NeoForge/Forge AND game version

3. Download the .jar files

4. On the Proxmox Ubuntu VM, open the Terminal:

5. (Stops the minecraft server)
sudo systemctl stop minecraft 

6. (Make a new directory to upload the mods)
mkdir -p /home/minecraft/minecraft-server/mods

7. (Go back to your actual computer and download the mod that fits your version and type)
Use this prompt for in the Command Prompt:
scp C:\Users\Username\Downloads\modfile.jar minecraft@privateIPaddress:/home/minecraft/minecraft-server/mods/

